    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "None."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Store and clear DTC"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If the vehicle is determined to have a fault, a temporary DTC is stored in the PGM-FI ECU memory. If the same failure is detected at the next D/C (two consecutive detections), the D indicator light will flash without the PGM-FI warning light illuminating, and the DTC and freeze data will be stored."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Use of the clear command of the scan tool (including HDS) or removal of the 12V battery terminal will clear the D indicator light, temporary DTC, DTC, and freeze data."
    }
  ],
